```

```js
const helmet = require('helmet');
app.use(helmet());  // Sets X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options, HSTS, CSP, etc.
```

---

### 3. No Rate Limiting
The `/users` endpoint (and any future endpoints) have no rate limiting, making them vulnerable to brute force and DoS attacks.

```bash
npm install express-rate-limit
```

```js
const rateLimit = require('express-rate-limit');

const limiter = rateLimit({
  windowMs: 15 * 60 * 1000, // 15 minutes
  max: 100,                  // Max 100 requests per window per IP
  standardHeaders: true,
  legacyHeaders: false,
});

app.use(limiter);
```

---

